<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Encelia farinosa </i>is fire sensitive and weakly sprouts after fire (Brown and Minnich 1986). However, it can rapidly colonize burned areas from off-site seed sources (Tesky 1993b). Stands replace those of <i>Artemisia californica, Eriogonum fasciculatum, </i>and <i>Salvia apiana </i>in mountains of southern California when fires are frequent.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
